% op-stack capture on `capture`: ambient op-stack items between the
% matched @delimit-barrier and the capture point are saved as a
% slice, trimmed from the live op stack (so handler sees clean op),
% and restored below the resume value on resume.
{ 42 { } capture add } delimit /k exch def 10 /k load exec pop
{ 1 2 3 { } capture add add add } delimit /k exch def 4 /k load exec pop
{ { dup is-continuation } capture } delimit pop
{ 100 200 300 { pop } capture } delimit clear
{ 5 { 10 exch abort-exec } capture add } delimit pop
